Quick install of Tmdet package:

> tar -xzvf Tmdet.tgz
> cd Tmdet
> cmake -B build
> make -C build
> sudo make -C build install


CONFIGURATION AND REQUIREMENTS

Environment variables can overwrite default settings:

- TMDET_DIRECTORY               (/usr/local/share/tmdet)
- CHEMICAL_COMPONENT_DIRECTORY  (/usr/local/share/tmdet/data/ccd)
- FRAGMENT_CIF_EXEC             (/usr/local/share/tmdet/fragment_cif)
- PDB_DATA_DIRECTORY            (/zfs/databases/UniTmp/PDB/data/structures/divided/updated_mmcif)
- UNITMP_SCHEMA                 (https://)
- UNITMP_DOMAIN                 (unitmp.org)

Chemical component directory is important during parsing CIF files.
This should be downloaded from WWPDB. There is a helper script to download it to a given directory:

> export CHEMICAL_COMPONENT_DIRECTORY=/usr/local/share/tmdet/data/ccd
> bash scripts/get-chemical-component-directory.sh $CHEMICAL_COMPONENT_DIRECTORY

Note: This script creates the target directory if it does not exist.

Another utility extracts and splits monomer CIFs from the downloaded components file:

> build/src/fragment_cif -i $CHEMICAL_COMPONENT_DIRECTORY/components.cif.gz -d $CHEMICAL_COMPONENT_DIRECTORY -s &> fragmenting.log
